HEADWORD: Homœomerous
<hw>Ho`m⟦oe⟧*om"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having the main artery of the leg parallel with
the sciatic nerve; -- said of certain birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

